houghts\n|\nAny coward can be a peacekeeper! In fact, that comes to one naturally. But they are blessed, the peacemakers...and all those who know the difference.\n\n- Criss\n|\nYou can do this by disciplining yourself to be selective in what you read, see, hear, say to yourself and the influence of others.\n\n- Mensah Oteh, Unlocking Life's Treasure Chest: Wisdom keys to keep you inspired, encouraged, motivated and focused\n|\nSummer grasses,All that remainsOf soldiers' dreams\n\n- Bashō\n|\nWe are all born stars, but some refuse to shine and others make it their life’s mission to glow.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nDo I believe that God is right here, ready to be my comfort in every situation?\n\n- Erin M. Straza, Comfort Detox: Finding Freedom from Habits That Bind You\n|\nIn visions of the night, like dropping rain, Descend the many memories of pain\n\n- Aeschylus, Agamemnon\n|\nI am not here to compete in the war of words, I am here to nurture the future of stories.\n\n- Jason\n|\nLife, unfortunately, doesn't seem to care what we want.\n\n- Richelle Mead, Last Sacrifice\n|\nAnd this gray spirit yearning in desireTo follow knowledge like a sinking star,Beyond the utmost bound of human thought.\n\n- Alfred\n|\nTo find universal peace, teach yourself and everyone else to be kind, compassionate, and forgiving.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nStill, they have one thing I envy. Humans, if nothing else, have the good sense to die.\n\n- Markus Zusak, The Book Thief\n|\nDepend upon it, sir, when a man knows he is to be hanged in a fortnight, it concentrates his mind wonderfully.\n\n- Samuel Johnson, The Life of Samuel Johnson LL.D. Vol 3\n|\nWhen you are motivated by the kindness and wellbeing of humanity, then nothing can scare or derail you.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nBut that's the thing with death. The whisper of it descent travels fast and wide, and people must've know I'd become a corpse because nobody even came to view the body.\n\n- Gayle Forman, Where She Went\n|\nHer skin smelled like the twilight moon and her eyes looked primal, like a hungry animal. She was darkness – dangerous, beautiful darkness.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nThere is nothing to save, now all is lost,but a tiny core of stillness in the heartlike the eye of a violet.\n\n- D.H.\n|\nIn sales, every prospect is a potential customer.\n\n- Rajen Jani, Once Upon A Time: 100 Management Stories\n|\nWell, it's a good life and a good world, all said and done, if you don't weaken.\n\n- Alan Sillitoe, Saturday Night and Sunday Morning\n|\nA daily dose of daydreaming heals the heart, soothes the soul, and strengthens the imagination.\n\n- Richelle E. Goodrich, Smile Anyway\n|\nDon't ignore your dreams, in them your soul is awake and you are your true self.\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, Pearls Of Eternity\n|\nHe was sounding the deeps of his nature, and of the parts of his nature that were deeper than he, going back into the womb of Time.\n\n- Jack London, The Call of the Wild\n|\nThey ex­pect­ed to lose. And there­fore, they lost. [..] Peo­ple who start think­ing deep dark thoughts in the mid­dle of a war start ex­pect­ing to lose.\n\n- Michael\n|\nUse all this life to make yourself a great writer, thoughtful and kind, slowly, surely over the years.\n\n- T.K.\n|\nMother Nature created God as a neurological anti-depressant sentiment, but Man tore that God apart into pieces and made citadels of differentiation out of them.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, The Krishna Cancer\n|\nForgiveness is brave, sets us free from darkness, and allows light to shine the sweet fragrance of life into our souls\n\n- Paul\n|\nIf we fear loss enough, in the end the things we possess will come to possess us.\n\n- Rachel Naomi Remen, Kitchen Table Wisdom: Stories That Heal\n|\nby the time you open your eyes, the world might have already changed.\n\n- Matsuri Hino, ヴァンパイア騎士 7\n|\nWhen things are at their blackest, I say to myself, 'Cheer up, things could be worse.' And sure enough, they get worse.\n\n- Robert\n|\nIf you stop feeding